<HEADLINE> U.S. Warns Americans against Travelling to Northwest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 10 (Xinhua) -- The United States on Tuesday
warned Americans against travelling to the tribal areas in the
Northwest Frontier Province of Pakistan because of threats to
their lives.
</P>
<P>
The travel warning was contained in a statement issued by the
State Department, which also said the U.S. embassy in Islamabad
had deferred all official travel to the areas.
</P>
<P>
The travel warning said Washington had received information
that strongly suggested extremists based in Afghanistan were
preparing to attack U.S. interests in Pakistan in the near future.
</P>
<P>
It said extremist groups inside Pakistan also made threats
against U.S. citizens and the U.S. government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
