<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macedonia to Hold Presidential Elections in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Macedonia will hold its
presidential elections on October 31, the Macedonian Information
Agency (MIA) said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
President of the Assembly of Macedonia Sav Klimovski has signed
a decision to set the date for the elections, the Macedonia's
official news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Preparatory work for the elections had started in Macedonia,
Klimovski said on Monday, noting he hoped the elections would be
held in fair and democratic atmosphere, presenting a real
competition of ideas, programs, policy views for the prosperity of
Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia's current president Kiro Gligorov, the country's
first president elected after it gained independence On November
20 in 1991, was elected in October 1994 for a five-year term.
</P>
<P>
The registration for the presidential elections will run from
August 24 to September 7 this year. MIA said that people who want
to race for the presidency have to collect the necessary 10,000
signatures to win the candidacy during the 15-day period.
</P>
<P>
The election campaign would start on October 1 and a candidate
may cancel his or her candidacy at least 30 days before the
election day, that is, before October 1, the MIA said.
</P>
<P>
If there is no winner in the first round of elections, the
second round will be held two weeks later, that is, On November
14, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
