<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-10 19:41 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sudan, Yemen Highlight Arab Solidarity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Sudan and Yemen have expressed
relief with the detente of the Arab ties and highlighted the
importance of Arab solidarity.
</P>
<P>
A joint statement issued here Tuesday after a meeting of the
Joint Higher Ministerial Committee urged Arab concerted efforts to
establish fair and comprehensive peace in the Middle East based on
the U.N. relevant resolutions and the land-for-peace principle.
</P>
<P>
It stressed the necessity of restoring all the occupied Arab
lands, the full and unconditional withdrawal of the Israeli troops
from Syrian Golan Heights and south Lebanon and the guarantee of
all legitimate rights of the Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
At a joint press conference here on Tuesday, Sudanese Foreign
Minister Mustafa Othman Ismail and Yemeni Deputy Prime Minister
and Minister of Foreign Affairs Abdul-Qader Ba-Jammal said their
countries would attach special importance to bilateral investment
and trade and the development of transport services to ensure the
broadest future cooperation between them.
</P>
<P>
Sudan and Yemen support holding an Arab summit to bring close
the views of the Arab countries and discuss the causes of the Arab
nation as well as the regional and international developments, the
two ministers said.
</P>
<P>
It is prime time for holding such summit to deal with the
challenges facing the Arab nations and form a united Arab position
on the issues of common interest, they added.
</P>
<P>
Ba-Jammal arrived here on Monday to attend the session of the
Joint Higher Ministerial Committee that wound up Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two sides signed seven agreements, documents on five
executive projects and two protocols on strengthening bilateral
cooperation in the economic and cultural areas and enhancing the
private investments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
