<HEADLINE> Arab Women Have Important Role in Society: Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni Parliament Speaker Abdullah
Bin Hussein Al-Ahmar has said Arab Muslim women have a significant
role in building the society and development process.
</P>
<P>
Al-Ahmar made the remarks at the regional conference of the Arab
Muslim Women Federation that started Tuesday afternoon with the
theme of "the Muslim Woman on the 21st Century Chart."
</P>
<P>
The conference, organized by the Sanaa-based regional office of
the World Muslim Women Federation in the Arab World, attracted
woman representatives from different Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
Al-Ahmar highlighted the necessity of respecting the woman rights
and employing them in the right positions. "The message of woman
is more profound and comprehensive than what an simple person
imagines," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The conference discussed a number of issues, including the
strategy and status of women in Islam and their role in bringing
up offsprings. 
