<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cypriot Church to Scrap Religious Engagement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, August 10 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus Orthodox Church has
decided to scrap religious engagement ceremonies as from October
in an effort to discourage sex before marriage, the Cyprus News
Agency (CNA) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was taken by the Church's highest body, the Holy
Synod, and priests read out a relevant circular at church
services across the island on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Church decided to scrap the engagement ceremonies because
it found people use the engagements as an excuse for cohabitation,
something it strongly rejects.
</P>
<P>
The Synod also learned that some people also use engagements as
a way of raising money since it is customary, just as it is at
weddings, for guests to give cash instead of gifts to the couple.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
