<HEADLINE> India Lodges Strong Protest Against Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 10 (Xinhua) -- India lodged a strong protest
Tuesday night with Pakistan for the "provocative activity" carried
out by a Pakistan military aircraft by intruding into the Indian
territory.
</P>
<P>
It also asserted that Pakistan was "entirely responsible" for
the incident including deaths of those on board.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan High Commissioner Ashraf Jehangrir Qazi was summoned
to the External Affairs Ministry by Foreign Secretary K.
Raghunath, who said that "it was a military aircraft that had
intruded Indian airspace and engaged in undesirable activity."
</P>
<P>
An external affairs spokesman said, "Whatever has happened is
entirely the responsibility of Pakistan including the deaths of
those who were in the aircraft."
</P>
<P>
He also indicated that there had been at least eight incidents
of airspace violations since July this year in Gujarat region.
</P>
<P>
All the incidents were in violation of the agreement between
the two countries on prevention of airspace violations signed in
April 1991, he added. 
</P>
