<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Build 521 New Schools in 1999/2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 10 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Ministry of
Education announced here Tuesday that it will spend more than 1.1
billion birr (137.5 million U.S. dollars) to build new schools and
upgrade the existing ones in the 1999/2000 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Some 498 primary, 21 secondary and two vocational schools will
be built in various parts of the country, while 377 primary
schools would be upgraded and 265 others renovated, public
relations chief of the ministry, Shimelis Letike said.
</P>
<P>
Besides, six boarding schools will also be constructed while
work on the construction of 160 primary schools in various parts
of the country will be finalized, he added.
</P>
<P>
The ministry in January 1998 launched a five-year educational
development program with an outlay of 1.62 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the government's efforts, primary school coverage in
the Horn of Africa country has increased to 41.8 percent from 34.7
percent 18 month ago, the ministry said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
