<HEADLINE> EDS-Update with Details No Confidence Motion Against Japanese Cabinet Submitted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Japan's largest opposition party,
the Democratic Party of Japan (DPJ) on Tuesday night submitted a
no confidence motion to the House of Representatives (lower house)
against the Cabinet of Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi.
</P>
<P>
The motion was filed at 11:50 p.m. (local time), Kyodo News
reported.
</P>
<P>
The DPJ's move came after the ruling Liberal Democratic Party (
LDP) and its partners on Monday forced through a House of
Councilors (upper house) committee a set of bills to allow
wiretapping in investigations of organized crimes.
</P>
<P>
The forcible passage of the bills by the LDP, its coalition
partner Liberal Party (LP) and the New Komeito party during DPJ
questions was an act of hostility, Shoji Motooka, head of the DPJ'
s upper house members said.
</P>
<P>
DPJ leader Naoto Kan said Monday that his party would submit a
no confidence motion against the cabinet to force a dissolution of
the lower house and scrap the bills. 
</P>
</TEXT>
