<HEADLINE> France Reaffirms Its Attachment to Status Quo of Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 10 (Xinhua) -- France reaffirmed on Tuesday its
attachment to the status quo of Jerusalem, after Israel walled up
a new window opened by Palestinians in the Muslim holy site of
Haram al-Sharif in eastern Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
"Our position on the holy city is known: No change of status
quo by any side before a solution is found in the talks on the
final status (of Jerusalem)," said French Foreign Ministry
assistant spokesman Francois Rivasseau.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that anything which touches Jerusalem is serious,
adding that "Any action which may by nature increase the tension
should be carefully avoided."
</P>
<P>
Under cover of darkness, Israeli police blocked early Tuesday
morning a window opened by WAQF, the charitable organization in
charge of Muslim holy sites in Jerusalem, to provide air and light
to basement rooms of Mosque Al-Aqsa, which is located at one end
of Haram al-Sharif.
</P>
<P>
The action provoked angry protests from the Palestinians and a
suicide attack on Tuesday near Jerusalem, in which the Palestinian
driver of an automobile was killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
