<HEADLINE> Greek Equity Prices Hit New Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Greek equity prices soared to new
records Tuesday with the general index on the Athens Stock
Exchange (ASE) ending 1.62 percent higher at 4,585.26 points.
</P>
<P>
This is the 35th record for the general index on the ASE this
year. On July 22, the ASE general index ended at 4,528.97 points.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE/ASE 20 index also rose 2.24 percent to 2,575.64 points
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 323 billion drachmas (about 1.07 billion U.S.
dollars), and advancers led decliners by 157 to 131 with another
six issues unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The miscellaneous and investment sector led the rising stock
market with ending 3.17 percent and 2.48 percent higher
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
