<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Appoints Special Envoy to Comoros </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Organization of African
Unity (OAU) chief Salim Ahmed Salim Tuesday appointed Mozambican
professional diplomat Francisco Madeira as the special envoy to
the Comoros as part of effort to secure an early solution to the
two-year crisis in the archipelago.
</P>
<P>
The mandate of Madeira would push the implementation of the
Antananarivo Agreement of April 1999 which provides for the
preservation of the unity and territorial integrity of the
Comoros, an OAU press release here said.
</P>
<P>
In undertaking his mission, Madeira will be guided by the
relevant decisions adopted by the OAU Council of Ministers and the
Assembly of Heads of State and Government held in Algerian capital
Algiers on July 8-10, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The special envoy will soon travel to the Comoros where he is
to meet political and military leaders of the country, the release
said.
</P>
<P>
Madeira used to be ambassador to Tanzania, Zimbabwe and
Botswana.
</P>
<P>
Being a member of the Mozambican government delegation, Madeira
also participated in talks with opposition Mozambique National
Resistance (Renamo) in Rome, Italy which brought peace to
Mozambique in 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
