<HEADLINE> Angola to Sell Foreign Pirate Ship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 10 (Xinhua) -- A foreign pirate ship apprehended
by the Angolan government will be sold through "particular
negotiations" after two unsuccessful auctions without potential
buyers, a source of the Maritime Tribunal said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The tribunal, responsible for the auction of the ship "Han
Nam-7", made such a decision due to the considerable cost of ship
maintenance caused by the delay of acquisition, said Evaristo
Quemba, head of the Maritime Tribunal.
</P>
<P>
Quemba said that the tribunal will designate a person for
negotiating with anybody interested in buying the ship.
</P>
<P>
"Han Nam-7", a ship belonging to a South Korean fishing company
 registered in Spain, was apprehended by the Angolan government on
October 22, 1998, when it stealthily entered the Angolan
territorial waters.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan tribunal tried and expelled the captain, and
imposed an over-four-million-U.S.-dollar fine on the fishing
company for illegal fishing in Angolan waters. The fishing
company gave up the ship due to the big amount of the fine.
</P>
<P>
"Han Nam-7" was twice put up at auction since the end of July,
at the prices of 4.437 million dollars and some two million
dollars respectively. But there were nobody interested in a ship
at that price. 
</P>
</TEXT>
