<HEADLINE> Create Scientific Social Environment to Fight Falun Gong: Commentary (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- China should strive to create a
civilized and scientific social environment to step up the fight
against Falun Gong, says a commentator's article to be carried in
the People's Daily tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
The emergence of the Falun Gong issue has in-depth social
causes and a complicated political background instead of being an
accidental phenomenon, the article says.
</P>
<P>
One of the major reasons for the organization of Falun Gong and
its founder Li Hongzhi to be able to fan the flames of disorder is
that ignorance and superstition prevail in some parts of the
country, the commentary says.
</P>
<P>
Since the policies of reform and opening up were introduced two
decades ago, China has scored outstanding achievements in its
economy, social progress and the building of socialist ethics.
</P>
<P>
But meanwhile, various ideologies swarmed in by taking
advantage of the opening environment. In some localities,
sorcerers and fortune-tellers have enjoyed booming business, with
some books, films and TV programs produced full of pseudo-sciences
and superstitions, it says.
</P>
<P>
Some party officials, including a handful in leading positions,
just shut their eyes to the phenomena, and some even participated
in superstitious practices, the commentary says.
</P>
<P>
Against such a social background, it is easy to understand the
urgency and importance of strengthening the building of socialist
ethics to create a civilized and scientific social environment, it
says.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990811.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Hongzhi's Political Motives and Serious Mischief: Commentary (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The 16th issue of the magazine
Seeking Truth carries a commentary on Li Hongzhi and the political
motives of his Falun Gong sect and its serious harm.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said that Li Hongzhi is interested in politics
and has conspicuous political ambitions, and his illegal Falun
Gong cult interfered in political and social issues and instigated
people to oppose the government.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi's ulterior motive is to grab the ideological
commanding heights from the Communist Party, it said. To achieve
this, he fabricated a whole set of absurd ideas, and made people
believe that his words were the only absolute truth in the world.
</P>
<P>
His remarks on Heaven and God, as well as Falun Gong's
rejection of other religious beliefs plainly reveal his aim of
overthrowing materialism and the Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
Winning people over by deceiving them was Li's major ploy to
achieve his political goal. He asked people to forsake social
activities, lose confidence in the government, and break away from
Communist Party leadership, the commentary said.
</P>
<P>
In this respect, Falun Gong is by no means an organization
devoted to promoting health, but a political tool with a rigorous
organization. Its task is to oppose the government with the
support of a vicious political force.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990811.0081 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Hongzhi's Political Motives and Serious Mischief: Commentary (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The commentary said that the Communist Party is the core of the
leadership of the Chinese people and the socialist cause. If
anything hampers this leadership, China will be in deep trouble.
</P>
<P>
If Falun Gong's influence is not curbed, the Party leadership
will be threatened. What Li preached is spiritualism, the opposite
of materialism, which Communist Party members believe.
</P>
<P>
Some Party members became addicted to superstitious thinkings
and lost the basic quality of being Communist Party members. Falun
Gong has undermined the Party's cohesiveness and must be
eliminated, the commentary stressed.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi and his followers stirred up incidents time and
again, seriously disrupting social order.
</P>
<P>
The late senior Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping stressed
repeatedly that "stability is the overwhelming issue for China.
Without stability, nothing can be achieved, and the fruits
already achieved will be lost soon or later."
</P>
<P>
Li also knew this very well, and because of this he tried every
means to cause social disorder. If Falun Gong had not been banned,
there would have been serious political repercussions, it said.
</P>
<P>
All in all, the commentary concluded, Li Hongzhi and his sect
have clear political motives and ambitions. The emergence and
expansion of Falun Gong have brought great harm to the people and
the Communist Party. The fight against Li Hongzhi is a political
one and will affect China's development. Its harmfulness must be
fully realized and its evil influences eliminated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
