<HEADLINE> Li Hongzhi's Political Motive and Serious Mischief: Commentary (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He deified himself and claimed to have supernatural powers. He
made people believe that he was the Savior. He may not understand
theology, but he wanted to be idolized by people, because through
this he could realize his political ambition.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi disseminated the claim that "the government is
useless" and cannot solve mankind's problems. He exaggerated China
's problems, directly accusing the Chinese government, the
commentry said.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of slandering the government was to replace it, the
commentary pointed out. Li's answer to the question of who could
solve the people's problems was that Falun Gong is the only law of
the human society, and that he was chosen by God to save the
mankind.
</P>
<P>
Li demanded that all people should turn to him for solutions.
He wished to control people through making them practice Falun
Gong and thereby come to idolize him, it said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the Falun Gong sect also tried every means to
corrupt the Communist Party of China. He cultivated adherents
among Party members and high-ranking officials. He wanted them to
break away from the Communist Party leadership and obey only him.
</P>
