<HEADLINE> India Accuses Pakistan of Firing at Its Helicopter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 11 (Xinhua) -- India accused Pakistan
Wednesday of firing a surface-to-air missile at its helicopter
carrying journalists to the site of the wreckage of the downed
Pakistani military aircraft in western area bordering with
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
However, a senior Indian Air Force (IAF) official here said the
Pakistani missile missed the target and "all the occupants of the
helicopter are safe".
</P>
<P>
The incident happened when one of the three helicopters
carrying journalists and officials to the wreckage site on the
Indian side of the international border in the western state of
Gujarat was targeted by a Pakistani surface-to-air missile.
</P>
<P>
"the helicopter immediately ducked and escaped being hit," the
official said, adding that the missile flew past the chopper by a
few hundred meters.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the helicopter, when attacked, was
four kilometers within Indian territory.
</P>
<P>
The journalists and officials could not reach the site of the
wreckage of the Pakistani Atlantique surveillance and
anti-submarine plane in the Kori Greek area by the Arabian Sea and
all the three choppers had to return to their base safely.
</P>
<P>
The official said that IAF had already taken precautions for
the visit of the journalists and fighter jet cover had been
provided. 
</P>
</TEXT>
