<HEADLINE> 359 Illegal Immigrants Captured in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Turkish security forces
Wednesday captured 359 illegal immigrants in two towns in Turkey,
the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that 103 foreign immigrants were captured in
Ipsala town of Edirne province as they were trying to proceed to
Greece illegally. Turkish eastern Edirne province borders Greece.
</P>
<P>
The immigrants, including two Romanians, 80 Iraqis, 18
Pakistanis and three Bangladeshis, were later taken into custody
for violating the Turkish borders and the passport law.
</P>
<P>
The other 256 illegal immigrants, including 251 Iraqis and five
Iranians, were seized in Saray town of eastern province of Van.
</P>
<P>
The illegal immigrants will be handed over to the Van Police
Organization to be deported after interrogation, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Turkish security officials said that all the immigrants will be
deported once the legal proceedings are completed.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that a total of 2,252 illegal immigrants were
captured in Ipsala town of Edirne province in the first seven
months of this year while they were trying to pass to Greece.
</P>
<P>
Some immigrants did not have passports and were planning to go
to other western European countries once they were in Greece.
</P>
</TEXT>
