<HEADLINE> Turkey Hopes Positive Solution on Turkish-Iranian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Turkey hoped that a positive
solution to be reached at the ongoing sixth meeting of the
Turkish-Iranian Higher Commission on Security, a Turkish Foreign
Ministry official said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry Deputy Spokesman Sermet Atacanli made the
remarks at a weekly press conference. He said that the meeting,
which began Tuesday in Ankara, is being held in a positive
atmosphere.
</P>
