the good will make the delegations of the two countries reach a
positive result at the end of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Iran released two Turkish soldiers, who were
detained by Iran after entering Iranian territory by mistake on
July 22, in a bid to ease tensions between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Local Hurriyet (Freedom) daily has said that Iran's release of
the two soldiers would show a "sign of goodwill" to Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Ties between the two countries were further strained after Iran
 claimed that Turkish warplanes attacked an Iranian military post
and tents belonging to Iranian tribesmen on July 18, during which
five people were killed and 10 others injured. 
</P>
