<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earthquake in Cyprus Causes Injuries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-five people were injured
or sustained a shock in an earthquake Wednesday, the Cyprus News
Agency (CNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake, measuring 5.8 on the Richter scale, occurred
at 07:27 a.m. local time (0427 GMT).
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the earthquake was in Gerasas region, north of
the southern coastal town of Limassol, but it was felt throughout
the island.
</P>
<P>
In Limassol, a Hospital First Aid spokesman said that two
persons suffered fractures when they jumped from the second floor
of a building to escape. Others were taken to the hospital in a
state of shock.
</P>
<P>
A Police spokesman said that there were numerous reports of
damage to homes in the Limassol district.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus is located in a seismic zone and earthquakes are
common.
</P>
<P>
In October 1996, the island was hit by a quake measuring 6.3 on
the Richter scale.
</P>
<P>
In February 1995, two people in the western Paphos region were
killed in an earthquake measuring 5.7 on the Richter scale, when
the roof of their home caved in.
</P>
<P>
Other tremors in recent years have caused little damage and no
loss of life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
