today in this provincial capital to denounce Lee Teng-hui's "two
states" remarks.
</P>
<P>
Ye Yongchang, president of the Guangdong Provincial Association
of Taiwan Compatriots, said that the "two states" statement
trotted out by Lee Teng-hui on July 9 has aroused strong
opposition from all people, including Taiwan compatriots, in
Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 2,000 Taiwan compatriots living in the province have
indignantly denounced, in various ways, Lee's remarks, he said.
</P>
<P>
Xu Jinxian, a representative of local Taiwan compatriots, said
that despite the fact that many countries have recently re-
affirmed that they only recognize one China, Lee Teng-hui still
insists on explaining his "two states" statement through Koo Chen-
fu and Taiwan's "Mainland Affairs Council".
</P>
<P>
Lee has attempted to fool the people under the pretense of
safeguarding the interests of Taiwan's people, but his true motive
of splitting the motherland remains unchanged, Xu said.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan compatriots attending the talks all agreed that what
Lee has done over the past ten years is aimed at splitting Taiwan
from China.
</P>
<P>
Lee's splittist remarks and actions have seriously damaged the
foundation for cross-straits relations and will bring catastrophe
to the people of Taiwan, as he is making a political adventure by
gambling with the future of Taiwan and the benefits, welfare and
fate of the 2.2 million people of Taiwan, they noted.
</P>
<P>
Peaceful reunification of the motherland is the inexorable
trend of history, and if Lee Teng-hui refuses to come to his
senses and continues his separatist activities, he is bound to
become a traitor to the Chinese nation, they said. 
</P>
