<HEADLINE> State Councilor: Drug Purchasing, Marketing Need Regulation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- State Councilor Wang Zhongyu has
urged relevant departments to intensify efforts to crack down on
unhealthy practices in the purchasing and marketing of
pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
He made the call here today at a televised national conference,
saying that straightening out the malpractices in this sector is
of great significance for the people's health and the building of
a clean government, as well as for the reform, development and
stability.
</P>
<P>
Wang called for stringent measures to ban the dozens of
illegally established drug distribution centers across the country.
He added that extra efforts are needed to strictly regulate the 17
authorized Chinese herbal medicine markets.
</P>
<P>
In addition, steps should be taken to bring into line
pharmaceuticals manufacturers who have multiplied chaotically in
recent years, Wang said, citing the prevalence of shoddy and fake
drugs, criminal activities such as giving and taking kickbacks,
and random pricing.
</P>
<P>
Hospitals and related institutions should tighten control over
drugs, and take resolute measures to establish separate accounts
and management systems for drug sales, he stressed. 
