<DOCNO> XIE19990811.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientists Slam Falun Gong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- More than 20 well-known Chinese
scientists attended a meeting today held by the China Association
for Science and Technology (CAST) to further expose and criticize
Falun Gong cult.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Guangzhao, vice-chairman of the National People's Congress
(NPC) Standing Committee and president of the CAST, said
scientists should think deeply about the Falun Gong phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
Falun Gong cult has poisoned the minds of many people and
undermined social stability by forming the illegal organization.
If the cult is allowed to develop, it will undermine the country's
drive to realize modernizations through science and technology,
said Zhou.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the fight against Falun Gong and pseudoscience will
last for a long time, he said, adding that scientists should
shoulder the responsibility to spread scientific knowledge and the
scientific spirit, methods, and attitude.
</P>
<P>
According to Hong Zhaoguang, a professor with the Beijing
Anzhen Hospital, more than 1.78 million senior citizens above the
age of 60 are now living in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Many of these elderly folks suffer from chronic diseases, and
Falun Gong cult deceived many of them with promises of improved
health, Hong said.
</P>
<P>
When asked why so many well-educated people believed in Falun
Gong, renowned physicist Zhao Zhongxian, who is also an
academician with the Chinese Academy of Sciences, said everyone
has limits in knowing the truth, the universe, and the society,
and scientists are no exception.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Guangzhao said Chinese scientists must study more
philosophy, which is the basis for scientific breakthroughs and
innovations.
</P>
<P>
Scientists attending today's meeting shared the opinion that it
is the responsibility of scientists to fight against superstition
and popularize science among ordinary people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
