shooting down of the Pakistani naval aircraft by Indian Air Force
was a premeditated hostile act on the part of India.
</P>
<P>
Director General of the Inter-Services Public Relations
Brigadier Rashid Qureshi said that there was a high-level contact
between the Directors General of Military Operations of India and
Pakistan and that if the Indians thought there was an aircraft
flying close to or within their airspace, they could have
contacted on the hot-line.
</P>
<P>
However, "no such action was done by the Indians, so it seems
to be a premeditated hostile act," Qureshi observed.
</P>
<P>
Qureshi said it was an unarmed naval aircraft which was on
routine training mission inside Pakistani airspace and the
wreckage of the aircraft was within Pakistani territory.
</P>
<P>
"It was unarmed, there was no hostile action committed by the
aircraft, in fact it was incapable of committing hostile act," he
added. 
