<HEADLINE> Container Transportation on Right Track </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Information from the Shanghai
Shipping Exchange Bureau shows that the monthly container
transportation operations of the China Shipping Group have
increased at a growth rate of 300 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate that the company's container transportation
volume in the first half of this year exceeded that in 1998, with
its income during the period overtaking that in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The company has occupied 70 percent of the domestic container
transport market and become the biggest one in the field, with
over 40 container ships.
</P>
<P>
It has also put 20 container ships with handling capacities of
1,000-3,000 TEUs each on international routes, including the China-
Australia and China-Europe routes, marking the entry of the
company's container transportation into the global market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
