<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Killed, 15 Injured in Thunderstorm in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and
15 others injured by a thunderstorm Tuesday in Phnom Penh,
according to Phnom Penh police Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A 50-year-old man was killed by thunder and lightning while a
two-year-old boy and a twenty-year-old man were covered up by the
collapsed houses. Among the 15 injured, six were in serious
condition, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, 112 houses were damaged and collapsed in the
rainstorm.
</P>
<P>
In last week's flash floods, at least five children drowned and
hundreds of families were left homeless as well as many rice
fields were destroyed. Damages amounted to nearly 300,000 U.S.
dollars, according to a government report.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Hun Sen has already asked the Finance Ministry
to disburse 1.1 billion riel (290,000 U.S. dollars) to provide
food, medicine and other aid to those who lost homes and rice
paddies in the flooding. 
</P>
</TEXT>
