<HEADLINE> Sensex Falls 40 Points in Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index dropped by
40.49 points Wednesday on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) in the
wake of late selling pressure triggered by fears of renewed border
tension and speculations.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share sensitive index dropped to the day's low of
4,502.97 points at the initial stages but later rallied smartly to
a high of 4,616.40 before falling back to close at 4,553.63 as
against Tuesday's close of 4,594.12, netting a loss of 40.49
points or 0.88 percent.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index dipped by 15.08 points to 2,012.71 from
previous close of 2,027.79.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the Dollex were quoted marginally down at
460.12 and 176.15 points compared with previous close of 463.10
and 177.48 respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
