<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Road Accident Kills 17, Injures 26 in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- At least 17 persons were killed
and 26 others injured, with five of them critically, in a road
accident in western Bangladesh's Pabna district early Wednesday
morning.
</P>
<P>
Police said the accident occurred on the Nagarbari-Bogra
highway in Pabna district, about 130 kilometers west of here, at
about 2:30 a.m. local time, when a night coach heading for
Thakurgaon district in northwestern Bangladesh from Dhaka hit a
standing truck loaded with iron rods, the BSS news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen passengers on the coach, including a woman, died on
the spot while 29 others were injured.
</P>
<P>
Three of the injured died on their way to hospital, and the
others were immediately taken to a nearby health complex.
</P>
<P>
It was not known what had caused the accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
