<HEADLINE> Indian Forces Steal Some Parts of Plane Wreckage: Pak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Indian armed forces traced
the wreckage of a Pakistan Navy (PN) plane and stole some of its
parts immediately after they shot down the plane, a PN spokesman
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He said the PN personnel, which found the wreckage after
several hours' search, had monitored activity of the Indian
helicopters near the site of the incident.
</P>
<P>
"They reached the spot immediately under a premeditated
exercise," he was quoted by the Associated Press of Pakistan as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The unarmed PN aircraft was shot down with 16 crew on board by
Indian fighter planes on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Pakistani government, the wreckage of the
plane was found about two kilometers inside Pakistani territory in
the Badin district in southern Sindh province.
</P>
<P>
The wreckage of the plane, scattered over an area of 1.5 miles,
is still there, said the spokesman, adding that the PN personnel
were manning the area.
</P>
<P>
"We are looking for the remains of our personnel martyred in
the cowardly attack by India," he said.
</P>
<P>
Some of the body parts had been founded by Tuesday evening
while further search is still going on, the spokesman said.
</P>
</TEXT>
