<DOCNO> XIE19990811.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Environment Ministers to Meet to Discuss Haze </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Minister for
Environment Lee Yock Suan has disclosed that ASEAN environment
ministers are looking at bringing forward their next meeting to
discuss the haze action plan of the region.
</P>
<P>
After attending a ceremony Tuesday to observe the 34th national
day of Singapore, Lee said that the meeting is to be hosted by
Singapore and scheduled for the end of this month with the exact
date yet to be fixed, media reports said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Lee attached importance to taking early action against forest
fires in the region, saying if the fires burn out of control, it
will be a very difficult situation, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Lee was quoted as saying that "Singapore continues to monitor
the haze very closely with the satellite monitoring system and is
providing information constantly to all the ASEAN neighbors,
especially to Indonesia and Malaysia."
</P>
<P>
"The Indonesian authorities have also given their pledge to
disallow open burning to clear land. Unfortunately at the ground
level, the implementation has not been up to expectation," he
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the reports, Lee noted that the areas in central
Sumatra and Kalimandan, Indonesia, where first fires have been
burning, were going through a dry period and he expressed his hope
that with greater attention focused by the authorities on this
issue there would be some improvement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
