<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand, Malaysia to Enhance Tourism Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia has proposed that
Thailand enhance tourism cooperation in an effort to reduce the
imbalance in tourist arrivals between the two countries, Thailand
News Agency (TNA) reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Minister of Culture, Arts and Tourism Dato Abdul
Kadir raised the idea to Tourism Authority of Thailand (TAT)
senior officials early this week, hoping to boost two-way tourist
traffic and organize joint promotion programs abroad, said the
report.
</P>
<P>
The proposal was accepted in principle by the TAT and the two
sides agreed to solve the problems of accessibility.
</P>
<P>
Both sides demanded more airline services to link Thai
destinations such as Phuket and Hat Yai with Malaysian resorts
Langkawi and Penang.
</P>
<P>
More than 1 million Malaysian tourists visit Thailand each year
while some 300,000 Thai tourists travel to Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Thailand and Malaysia will now jointly promote overseas
markets. Thailand is expecting more than 8 million tourist
arrivals this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
