<HEADLINE> Rivaldo Thinking of Lucrative Deal With Barcelona </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Rivaldo was looking forward to a
high appeciation from the Spain's giant Barcelona, pledging a
lucrative new contract with the Catalan club.
</P>
<P>
Provoked by a big offer from England's Europe champion
Manchester United, the Brazilian midfielder thought his improving
status should cost Barcelona much.
</P>
<P>
"My representative will now meet with Barcelona to make sure I
stay happy and that I'm being valued here," said Rivaldo, who came
back to the Nou Camp after his summer vocation in Brazil on
Wednesday in Barcelona.
</P>
<P>
"If I'm being so highly valued outside Spain, it's important
that I'm also appreciated by Barcelona," Rivaldo added.
</P>
<P>
Reports said Manchester United are bidding a 50 million U.S.
dollars for the Brazilian, who is tagged as one of the best
footballers in the world.
</P>
<P>
Rivaldo now is under contract with Barcelona until 2002.
</P>
</TEXT>
