<HEADLINE> Indonesia's New Legislators to be Inducted on Oct. 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government and
the speaker of the House of Representatives (DPR) and the People's
Consultative Assembly (MPR) have agreed to induct the new
legislators on October 1, according to the Antara News Agency.
</P>
<P>
In a consultative meeting here Wednesday, President B.J.
Habibie who represented the government, House Speaker Harmoko and
other ranking government officials also agreed to make legal the
results of the vote count of the June 7 general election.
</P>
<P>
Harmoko said the new legislative body will draw up its agenda,
including the appointment of the next president and vice president
as well as House speaker, and the formation of the House factions.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed that political party leaders and the people
implement the reform agenda constitutionally.
</P>
<P>
The House has so far deliberated 49 bills. The next legislative
body will discuss several bills, including those on the press and
security.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was attended by Coordinating Minister for Political
and Security Affairs Feisal Tanjung, Coordinating Minister for
Economy, Finance and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita, Coordinating
Minister for the People's Welfare Haryono Suyono, State
Secretary/Justice Minister Muladi, Defense Minister/Armed Forces
Chief Gen. Wiranto and Information Minister Yunus Yosfiah.
</P>
