<HEADLINE> Mine Blast Kills 9 Policemen in Eastern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The eastern city of Sri Lanka
Batticaloa Wednesday noon was rocked by a powerful claymore mine
blast, which killed nine policemen and injured 14 others, informed
sources here said.
</P>
<P>
The blast occurred in front of the police station in
Batticaloa, about 300 kilometers northeast of Colombo, said the
sources.
</P>
<P>
The blast is believed to be the work of Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam (LTTE) rebels, who have been fighting a 16-year-old
war for a separate Tamil state in the country. 
</P>
