<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Best Place to View Solar Eclipse: Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Turkish experts have said the
best country is Turkey to view the solar eclipse which occurs on
Wednesday, adding the eclipse can be viewed partially and totally
in the country.
</P>
<P>
Turkish people, waiting for the coming of the final solar
eclipse in the 20th century, have prepared special protective
glasses to be used at the legendary moment.
</P>
<P>
The total eclipse occurs at 2:20 p.m. local time on Wednesday
in Turkey's Black Sea city of Cide and leave the country's
viewing area at 2:42 p.m. in same day in Cizre, southeastern
Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The total eclipse can be viewed for two-and-a-half minutes
throughout Turkey.
</P>
<P>
European countries in which the solar eclipse can be seen
include Britain, France, Germany, Austria, Hungary, Romania and
Bulgria.
</P>
<P>
After it sweeps across Turkey, it will be seen in Iran,
Pakistan and die over the Indian Ocean.
</P>
<P>
Experts have warned people to take necessary precautions
while viewing the eclipse.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's Kandilli Observatory General Director Professor Ahmet
Mete Isikara said special protective glasses should be worn
when viewing the eclipse and children should be supervised by a
parent while viewing it.
</P>
<P>
He added that one should not stare longer than two minutes and
should take 15-20 seconds breaks from viewing.
</P>
<P>
Experts pointed out that children and those who have had
cataract surgery are under increased risk of damaging their eyes.
</P>
<P>
They warned people not to use glass, sun glasses, computer
diskettes, colored rolls of film, x-ray film, telescopes or
binoculars during totality. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990811.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 08:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heat Wave to Strike Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- A heat wave will strike Cyprus
in the coming days, pushing temperatures well above 40 degrees
Celsius in Nicosia, Cyprus' Meteorological Service said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday the mercury in capital Nicosia will be peg out at
39 degrees Celsius, Director of the Meteorological Service
Cleanthis Philaniotis said.
</P>
<P>
"We expect a rise in temperature from Thursday, to reach 40 or
higher in the central plain of Cyprus", until Saturday, he said.
</P>
<P>
A serious heat wave killed about 70 people in Cyprus in the
summer last year.
</P>
<P>
The Health Ministry has urged the public to take some
preventive measures to keep from a recurrence of last year's
heat-wave tragedy.
</P>
<P>
Citizens are advised to avoid frequent exposure to the sun,
especially when making some unnecessary movements and physical
exercises.
</P>
<P>
They are also urged to avoid alcohol, rich foods and to drink
plenty of water and liquids in general. 
</P>
</TEXT>
