<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 22nd Postal Congress Features Advanced Computer Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The 22nd Congress of the
Universal Postal Union (UPU) in Beijing later this month will
employ a state-of-the-art computer network system for voting,
information dissemination, and other purposes.
</P>
<P>
The secretariat of the Congress's organizing committee told
Xinhua that the new system has undergone thorough test runs to
ensure their smooth operation at the Congress.
</P>
<P>
For the first time, delegates will be offered the alternative
of making applications via the Internet. The on-line application
system was opened earlier in March, according to the secretariat.
</P>
<P>
The computer network, which used to serve the UPU only, has
been extended to hotels accommodating the Congress delegates, and
delegates will have Internet access to UPU networks in Switzerland
for all the information provided by UPU without leaving their
hotels.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the electronic voting system, the brainchild
of Chinese researchers, will use hundreds of monitors to display
results and information, in place of the old practice of
displaying them on screens.
</P>
<P>
During the Congress, some 500 bills will be discussed and voted
on, and the new voting system will greatly facilitate the entire
process, officials with the secretariat said.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that China will use such technology as
host of an international conference, said Cheng Yongping, in
charge of equipment management in the secretariat.
</P>
<P>
Total investment for the new systems is about 10 million yuan (
1.2 million U.S. dollars), and several companies including Compaq
and Hewlett-Packard have donated their products in support of the
Congress.
</P>
<P>
The 22nd UPU Congress, the first UPU meeting ever held in China,
is slated for August 23 to September 15 in Beijing. More than 2,
000 delegates from the 189 member nations of UPU and over 20
international organizations will attend the conference.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
