<HEADLINE> Kenya to Issue $135 Million Bonds to Offset Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan government will issue
one billion shillings (about 13.5 million U.S. dollars) worth of
special bonds so as to offset outstanding debt next Monday, the
Daily Nation newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The bonds will begin trading at the Nairobi Stock Exchange from
August 23, a source at Treasury said.
</P>
<P>
This move was in the wake of the successful issue of one
billion shillings worth of similar bonds early last month. The
first batch of bonds were floated in mid-July and snapped up by
investors in only three days of trading.
</P>
<P>
Large amounts of foreign debt is maturing this year and Kenyan
Finance Ministry has pledged not to default on it.
</P>
<P>
Kenya had external debt of some 4.4 billion dollars in May,
treasury and central bank figures showed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
