<HEADLINE> China Welcomes Press Coverage of National Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The world's media are welcome to
cover Beijing's  celebrations marking the 50th anniversary of the
founding of the People's Republic of China (PRC), a press
official announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Long Xinmin, deputy head of the press section of the
Preparatory Committee for Celebrating the 50th Anniversary of the
PRC, said that many large celebrations are expected to be held in
Beijing around October 1, and that reporters from overseas are
welcome to cover the events.
</P>
<P>
Foreign reporters can apply for coverage at Chinese embassies
and consulates in their countries, the Office of Commissioner of
Ministry of Foreign Affairs of China in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR), and the Macao Visa Office of the
Ministry of Foreign Affair of China.
</P>
<P>
Reporters from Taiwan should apply at the Taiwan Affairs Office
of the State Council, and foreign reporters based in China can
directly apply at the Information Department of the Chinese
Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Overseas reporters and reporters from Hong Kong, Macao and
Taiwan should show their certificates from their new organizations
upon application and specify whether they are print journalists or
photographers, he added.
</P>
<P>
Applications can begin on August 15 and the deadline is
September 15.
</P>
<P>
A press center will be set up in Beijing during the events to
provide information and relevant materials to reporters, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
