<HEADLINE> Lucent Introduces NetCare Service to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Lucent Technologies today
announced the introduction of NetCare Services in China and the
opening of its Asia/Pacific NetCare Service Center in Australia to
help customers plan and manage their communications networks.
</P>
<P>
NetCare is built on the company's network support services to
meet growing customer demand for planning, designing, integrating,
managing, maintaining and operating networks.
</P>
<P>
"The new service will enable our customers to spend more time
and energy on their businesses instead of on the operation of
their networks," said Bill Wallis, vice president of Customer
Program Management, Lucent Technologies China.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, no company has provided an entire package of network
support services in China.
</P>
<P>
Lucent has also merged with International Network Services (INS)
, a move which will boost the company's network service business
in China, said Wallis.
</P>
<P>
The U.S.-based Lucent Technologies operates in over 90
countries and is one of the world's leading communications
companies. In China, it has established seven regional offices,
eight joint ventures, and two wholly owned subsidiaries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
