<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines to Distribute Rice Seedlings to Calamity-hit Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government will
distribute rice seedlings to areas heavily hit by floods to help
farmers recoup their losses, Philippine News Agency reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Secretary Edgardo Angara of the Department of
Agriculture as saying Tuesday night that the seedlings would be
distributed in Ilocos, Central Luzon, the Southern Tagalog region,
and the Cordillera Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
He said the four regions suffered heavy damage to agriculture
as a result of the flash floods caused by continues monsoon rains
earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
Angara assured the public that there is more than enough supply
of seedlings for farmers to replant rice in 130,000 hectares in
Central Luzon alone.
</P>
<P>
According the National Disaster Coordination Council, the total
damage in the central Philippine areas was placed at 786 million
pesos (17.2 million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
