<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Launch Fresh Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's ruling Taliban
Wednesday launched a pre-dawn offensive across frontlines north of
Kabul and captured two districts, a media report reaching here
said.
</P>
<P>
The militia managed to take Sarai Khawaja and Kalakan districts
from forces loyal to opposition commander Ahmad Shah Masood and
pushed forward to 30 kilometers north of Kabul, said the
Pakistan-based Afghan Islamic Press (AIP).
</P>
<P>
At least 13 troops from both sides were killed and 24 others
were injured in heavy fighting, said AIP.
</P>
<P>
No confirmation from the Taliban authorities or the opposition
side is available so far.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban hold nearly 90 percent of Afghanistan and have been
fighting to remove former defense minister Masood, the last
obstacle to their complete control of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
