<HEADLINE> "Two States" Statement Damages Taiwan People's Interests (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The "two states" statement by
Taiwan leader Lee Teng-hui has seriously undermined relations
across the Taiwan Straits and hurt the interests of the people in
Taiwan, according to Taiwan specialists in the mainland province
of Fujian.
</P>
<P>
Wu Nengyuan, president of the Fujian Provincial Social Science
Academy's Modern Taiwan Institute, says that Lee's statement
places new obstacles in the way of economic and trade relations
across the Straits and could mean risks or economic losses for
Taiwanese investing in the mainland.
</P>
<P>
Exchanges between Taiwan and Fujian have been on the rise since
the 1980s and there are more than 5,000 Taiwan-financed businesses
in Fujian with huge investment stake. Many of them ship in raw
materials from Taiwan, process them, and then ship them back to
Taiwan as finished products, helping the economy of both Fujian
and Taiwan.
</P>
</TEXT>
