<BODY>
<HEADLINE>   Sydney to Be Smoke-free Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Sydney announced a bad news for
smokers on Wednesday when organizers approved a policy that
Smoking will be banned in spectator areas inside Olympic and
Paralympic venues at next year's Games.
</P>
<P>
This includes venue seating areas, bars and restaurants, the
living quarters and eating areas of the Games villages, the
sponsor hospitality suites and Games transport vehicles. Outdoor
venues will have a designated smoking area.
</P>
<P>
The policy had taken two years to develop by SOCOG's medical
progaram, said Sydney Organising Committee for the Olympic Games
deputy chief executive Jim Sloman.
</P>
<P>
The ban, including the Main Press Center and the International
Broadcast Center, will remain in place at the venues after the
Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
