<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Cereal Production Target Set at 23 Mln Tons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's cereal production
target for the current 1999-2000 fiscal year has been set at 23.03
million tons, 1.1 million tons more than that of the previous
fiscal year, The Financial Express newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In the last fiscal year, the cereal production was estimated at
21.93 million tons, an official of the Agriculture Ministry was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The target of cereal production fixed for the current fiscal
year would be possible to reach if there is no heavy crop-loss, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The production target of various kinds of rice has been fixed
at 20.91 million tons while that of wheat production at 2 million
tons and maize production at 120,000 tons, according to the plan
worked out by the Agricultural Ministry.
</P>
<P>
A series of measures have already been planned to provide
vigorous support to farmers to reach the target, he said.
</P>
<P>
Such measures, he added, include encouragement to the use of
more urea super granules, high yielding varieties of seeds,
balanced fertilizer and supplementary irrigation to meet any
draught situation if occurs in October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
