</P>
<P>
LONDON -- The UK economy is showing clear signs of recovery,
according to new figures released Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Confidence in the manufacturing industry has improved for the
first time in 18 months, and High Street or consumer spending rose
for the second month in a row. However, both sectors say
conditions are still tough, and warn that an increase in interest
rates could have an adverse effect. (UK-Economy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Mexico's trade deficit in the first half of the
year fell 28.7 percent to 2.1 billion U.S. dollars compared with
the same period in 1998, the Treasury Secretary said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Total merchandise export during this period rose to 63.7
billion dollars, up 10 percent over a year ago, while total
merchandise import was 65.8 billion dollars, up 8.1 percent. (
Mexico-Trade Deficit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
