BUENOS AIRES -- Argentina registered a trade surplus of 112
million U.S. dollars in the first half of this year, said the
Ministry of Economy on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It said that exports totaled 11.95 billion dollars, down by 12
percent from the same period of last year, and that imports
declined by 25 percent to 11.84 billion dollars. (Argentine-Trade
Surplus)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
