<HEADLINE> Argentina Registers Trade Surplus in First Half Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Argentina registered a
trade surplus of 112 million U.S. dollars in the first half of
this year, said the Ministry of Economy on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It said that exports totaled 11.95 billion dollars, down by 12
percent from the same period of last year, and that imports
declined by 25 percent to 11.84 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of 1998, the country's exports totaled 13.58
billion dollars and imports 15.75 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Primary products accounted for 29 percent of the total exports
in the first six months of 1999, agricultural products for 30
percent, and industrial products for 31 percent.
</P>
<P>
The ministry noted that the overseas sales of primary products
were 13 percent lower than in the same period of 1998, while those
of industrial products shrank 25 percent.
</P>
