" remark, he has met condemnation from Chinese at home and abroad,
and criticism from the international community, the article says.
</P>
<P>
 China Daily
</P>
<P>
-- China calls for a bigger media role in encouraging
manufacturers and consumers alike to give priority to product
quality, and eventually driving all inferior products out of the
market.
</P>
<P>
"Media reports have proved to be an effective way of supervising
product quality and informing consumers of legal weapons to
protect themselves against substandard products," said an official
with the State Quality and Technical Supervision Administration.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese ambassador to Japan Chen Jian lashes out at Falun
Gong, expressing the hope that the international community can
understand the Chinese government action against the cult.
</P>
