<HEADLINE> Croatia Reports Less Forest Fires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Croatia, a country with half of
its land covered with forests, reported drastically less forest
fires in the first seven months this year due to a series of
preventive steps taken by the government.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,116 forest fires were reported during this period,
just half of the number reported during the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
The average area burnt by each fire this year was five hectares
as compared with 16 hectares last year.
</P>
<P>
The reduction of forest fires is attributed to a package of
government measures, including extensive publicity, closer
cooperation between professional and voluntary firemen and
improved equipment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
