<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 10 (Xinhua) -- After winning three straight
events, American Pete Sampras will put his 17-match winning streak
on the line against Dutchman Jan Siemerink Tuesday night in second-
round action at the 2.2 million U.S. dollars ATP Championship in
Cincinnati, the United States.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, one of eight seeds to receive a first-round bye, has
not lost since a second-round upset to Andrei Medvedev of Ukraine
at the French Open, collecting titles at the Stella Artois
Championship, Wimbledon and the Mercedes-Benz Cup.
</P>
<P>
