Grosjean 7-5, 6-3; No. 14 Albert Costa of Spain got past Australia
's Andrew Ilie 6-4, 3-6, 6-2; and No. 15 Nicolas Lapentti of
Ecuador ousted 1998 quarterfinalist Vincent Spadea of the United
States 6-2, 6-2. 
