<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in Vietnam Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnamese government granted
investment licenses to 138 foreign projects with a combined
capital of almost 798 million U.S. dollars in the first 7 months
of this year, Vietnam's English daily Vietnam News reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
But the figures amounted to 90 percent of the number of
projects and 59 percent of the capital attracted in the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
During January-July, 66 projects applied to increase their
capital by a combined 294.5 million U.S. dollars, a 33 percent
rise over last year's corresponding period.
</P>
<P>
The total foreign capital flow into the country during the 7
months was more than 1 billion U.S. dollars and foreign investment
disbursed was 896 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-invested enterprises in Vietnam are enjoying an
increasing growth rate. They grossed in the past seven months 1.38
billion U.S. dollars of export value, up 21 percent, and 2.3
billion U.S. dollars of turnover, a 24 percent increase.
</P>
<P>
The foreign-invested sector employed 281,000 workers by the end
of July, up eight percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The sector's industrial production, in particular, grew 21
percent to account for almost 35 percent of the national
industrial production value.  
</P>
</TEXT>
