<HEADLINE> Pole Vault All Time Great Bubka out of Seville </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine's six-time world pole
vault champion Sergei Bubka will not defend his title in the next
week's world athletics championships in Seville, Spain.
</P>
<P>
Bubka, who has long been plagued with an ankle injury, has not
competed at one meeting this year, and he has pulled out of
Seville on the advice of a Helsinki doctor.
</P>
<P>
Although he was a doubtful starter, the 35-year-old sporting
legend's name was still on Ukraine's selection list to compete at
the championships, which will open on August 20.  
</P>
</TEXT>
