<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Hold High-Tech Fair In September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, August 11 (Xinhua) -- A national fair displaying and
trading high-tech achievements will be hosted in the coastal city
of Qingdao in east China's Shandong Province on September 7-10.
</P>
<P>
During the four-day event, the largest of its kind in China,
eighteen renowned high-tech research institutes and centers, over
30 prestigious universities including Qinghua and Fudan, and more
than 1,000 key state enterprises will participate.
</P>
<P>
They will host academic seminars, conduct business exchanges,
and seek cooperation opportunities in high-tech research
achievements and production.
</P>
<P>
Since 1991, Qingdao has hosted nine city-level high-tech
achievement fairs, signing a total of 617 contracts involving
investments of 153.6 million yuan (about 18 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
More than one-third of the local enterprises have established
long-term cooperative relations with many educational institutes
and research centers nationwide. Every year, 400 new high-tech
products, half of these enterprises' total, are realized through
cooperative endeavors.
</P>
<P>
The fair is jointly sponsored by the State Economic and Trade
Commission, the Ministry of Education, and the Municipal
Government of Qingdao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
