<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Falun Gong Discarded by Former Practitioners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Many former practitioners of
Falun Gong say that the cult has harmed their physical and mental
health, and vow never again to have anything to do with it.
</P>
<P>
Peng Haiyun, an employee of the railway station in this capital
of southwest China's Yunnan Province, started to practice Falun
Gong in January 1997, with the hope of curing his chronic ill
health.
</P>
<P>
But under his influence, his 26-year-old daughter, perfectly
well and just married then, started to practice Falun Gong too.
After a few months, she developed a big tumor on the thigh, but
refused to consult a doctor.
</P>
<P>
"Three months later, her condition grew worse, until she could
not even walk. We sent her to a hospital, where she was diagnosed
as suffering from advanced heart disease. But after a month's
medical treatment, her illness was stabilized." Peng said.
</P>
<P>
However, when they returned home they gave up all medical
treatment and started to practice Falun Gong again. "But this time
it was too late to save may daughter's life," Peng said with
remorse.
</P>
<P>
Also in Kunming, another 20 former practitioners of Falun Gong
demonstrated their determination to sever all their connections
with the cult in another way.
</P>
<P>
On the morning of August 2, they went to a local army hospital
with a letter of gratitude and a brocade flag to thank the doctors.
</P>
<P>
They had suffered because they had heeded the fallacies of
Falun Gong. The doctors at the hospital had gone to their homes to
persuade them to abandon Falun Gong. They gave timely treatment
and actually saved many of their lives.
</P>
<P>
Now the former practitioners have vowed never to have any thing
to do with the cult any more, having concluded that only science
can make their lives better. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
