<HEADLINE> Soerensen Wins 1st Stage of Tour of Denmark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOLKHOLM, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Danish cyclist Rolf Soerensen
won the first leg of Tour of Denmark and grabbed the leader's
yellow jersey at the 186 kilometers from Aalborg to Aarhus on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
After 172 kilometers, Soerensen pulled away from leading pack
of 16 riders and crossed the finish line 17 seconds ahead of Italy
's Nicola Loda of Ballan and Dane Lars Michaelsen of the French-
American team Francaise des Jeux/Saturn.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's stage included five hills and a cobblestone stretch.
</P>
