<HEADLINE> Ecuadorian President to Visit Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Ecuadorian President Jamil Mahuad
will hold an official meeting with Peruvian President Alberto
Fujimori during his Peru visit beginning Wednesday, Peru's Foreign
Ministry announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be the first of this nature between the two
presidents since the Brasilia peace accord between the two
countries took effect three month ago.
</P>
<P>
Peru and Ecuador ended a 100-year-old border dispute with the
erection of the last boundary mark on their common borders on May
13. 
