<HEADLINE> Morariu Ousts Testud in Acura Classic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Corina Morariu of the United
States beat eighth-seeded Sandrine Testud of France 6-1, 6-3 on
Tuesday in the first round of the Acura Classic in Manhattan Beach,
California.
</P>
<P>
Morariu, 2-1 in her career against Testud, teamed with Lindsay
Davenport to win the doubles title at Wimbledon in July, and they
followed that with titles at Stanford and La Costa.
</P>
<P>
Seventh-seeded Barbara Schett of Austria also advanced, beating
Ines Gorrochategui of Argentina 6-3, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
American Lisa Raymond, celebrated her 26th birthday by
eliminating Wimbledon semifinalist Mirjana Lucic of Croatia, 6-3,
6-1. Raymond, a qualifier, needed only 55 minutes to beat her 17-
year-old opponent.
</P>
<P>
In other first-round matches, Ruxandra Dragomir of Romania
rallied to beat Anne Kremer of Luxembourg 2-6, 7-6 (10-8), 6-2;
Patty Schnyder of Switzerland defeated Magui Serna of Spain 6-3, 6-
4;and Natasha Zvereva of Belarus outlasted Irina Spirlea of
Romania 6-4, 6-7 (7-4), 7-5.  
</P>
</TEXT>
