<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexican Trade Deficit Falls in First Half Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 10 (Xinhua) -- Mexico's trade deficit in
the first half of the year fell 28.7 percent to 2.1 billion U.S.
dollars compared with the same period in 1998, the Treasury
Secretary said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Total merchandise export during this period rose to 63.7
billion dollars, up 10 percent over a year ago, while total
merchandise import was 65.8 billion dollars, up 8.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Monthly export hit 12 billion dollars in June, the highest ever
in the country's history. It represented a 16.4 percent jump over
the same month last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990811.0302 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Teenagers Taught to Defend Themselves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- China has initiated a nationwide
education program that aims to teach teenagers how to protect
themselves when harassed or attacked, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
About 400 teenagers received tips and lessons on self-
protection Tuesday at Huangcun No.2 Middle School, located in
Beijing's suburban Daxing County.
</P>
<P>
Several programs were presented to teach the teenagers how to
fight back when attacked. Lectures focusing on physical and
psychological health care were also given, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The teenagers were also told where to go if they need legal
assistance or protection.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the program was to better prepare the teenagers
when they are confronted with psychological problems, disasters or
accidents.
</P>
<P>
China's youth organization, the Communist Youth League Central
Committee, has called on all its subcommittees at provincial
levels to improve their efforts to help the youngsters learn how
to respond when difficult situation arise.
</P>
<P>
The country now has 360 million people under the age of 18, the
paper said.
</P>
<P>
"The school has set up a good example for the whole society,"
said Zhao Yong, secretary of the secretariat of the committee.
</P>
<P>
Sources at the Beijing Adolescents' Rights Protection
Commission revealed that of the 400 teenagers who took part in the
camp, 90 percent said it was helpful, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
