<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arsenal Beats Derby County in Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dutch international Dennis Bergkamp put his side top when he
took a fine pass from French midfielder Emmanuel Petit in the 47th
minute and controlled it beautifully before beating Mark Poom in
the Derby goal.
</P>
<P>
Petit had given the Gunners the lead after 40 minutes with a
superb swinging 30-meter shot. But Rory Delap equalised on
halftime with a stunning volley from even further out that skimmed
past Arsenal keeper Alex Manninger.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal, who beat Leicester City by the same score in their
season-opener on Saturday, are the only club with a 100 percent
record of the eight teams who have played twice.
</P>
<P>
Middlesbrough rebounded from its opening-day 1-0 home defeat by
newly promoted Bradford City by beating Wimbledon 3-2 in London
after conceding the opening goal.
</P>
<P>
Sunderland put aside the memory of its 4-0 trouncing by Chelsea
to defeat Watford, the team promoted with it, 2-0. 
</P>
</TEXT>
