<HEADLINE> Bayern Munich Beat Benfica in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LISBON, August 10 (Xinhua) -- German champions Bayern Munich
beat Benfica 2-1 in a soccer friendly on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Michael Tarnat put Bayern up in the 65th minute, Sebastian "
Chano" Fernandez equalized the score in the 74th minute.
</P>
<P>
Alexander Zickler sealed the win for the visitors four minutes
before the final whistle in front of a sell-out partisan crowd of
65,000. 
</P>
