<HEADLINE> Argentine Stocks Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 10 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index of
the Buenos Stock Exchange went down by 0.71 percent to 463.20
points on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 15.980 million dollars against 13.891 million
dollars on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The annual interbank rate of interest fell to 5.75 percent in
the 24-hour term, compared with 6.10 on Monday. The parity of the
peso against the dollar remained unchanged at 0.997 for purchase
and 1.002 for sale. 
</P>
</TEXT>
