<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Slightly Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 10 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock exchange
closed Tuesday with the Benchmark IPC index reducing by 13.39
points, or 0.26 percent, to 5,058.31.
</P>
<P>
Operators changed 49.603 million shares for about 79.678
million dollars against 43.544 million shares worth 54.300 million
U.S. dollars on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, the peso, stood at 9.60 to one dollar for
sale and 9.30 for purchase in the main exhcnage houses of Mexico
city, maintaining unchanged as Monday. 
</P>
