<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest China City to Hold Lantern Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Zigong City in southwest China's
Sichuan Province will feature varieties of colored lanterns in a
grand show scheduled for January 28 to March 26 next year.
</P>
<P>
During the two-month festival in the new century, fifty sets of
huge colored lanterns and thousands of handicraft lanterns from
other cities across China will be on display, along with exotic
lanterns brought by a dozen countries and regions around the world.
</P>
<P>
Zigong's lantern shows date back 1,300 years to the Tang
Dynasty. Since the 1980s, the city has put on 50 large lantern
shows in 40 cities across China and in seven countries including
Singapore, Thailand, and Japan, attended by more than 50 million
people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
