<DOCNO> XIE19990811.0316 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Calls For Gun Control Intensification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 10 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
urged the nation Tuesday to "intensify our resolve to make America
a better place" in the face of shooting in Los Angeles and
suggested the shootings again showed the need for tighter gun
control laws.
</P>
<P>
"Once again, our nation has been shaken and our hearts torn by
an act of gun violence," Clinton said at a press conference at the
White House.
</P>
<P>
A man with a high-powered gun burst into a Jewish community
center in Los Angeles Tuesday and sprayed the lobby with 20 to 30
shots, wounding five people, including three boys attending day
camp, and then walked away.
</P>
<P>
Police searched the center grounds and the surrounding suburban
neighborhood for the man, described as a bald white male around 40
years old.
</P>
<P>
Clinton said he had been getting updates on the search for the
gunman, and called the shootings "another senseless act" and
offered federal assistance to local law enforcement agencies.
</P>
<P>
The violence was the latest in a series of shootings at
workplaces and schools in the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
